title: Witten conjecture
summary: In algebraic geometry, the Witten conjecture is a conjecture about intersection numbers of stable classes on the moduli space of curves, introduced by Edward Witten in the paper WittenÂ (1991), and generalized in Witten (1993). Witten's original conjecture was proved by Maxim Kontsevich in the paper Kontsevich (1992).
